    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to Acting
                        Secretary of State <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lenox, Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 193.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to Mr. O’Beirne’s note No. 99 of
                    the 9th of May [not printed], I have the honor to transmit to you herewith a
                    revised list of the staff of His Serene Highness Prince Louis of Battenberg and
                    of the captains of the ships of the second cruiser squadron who will accompany
                    the rear-admiral on his forthcoming visit to Washington.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. M. Durand.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>[Inclosure.]</head>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="italic">Staff of H. S. H. Prince Louis of Battenberg.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <list>
                        <item>Flag captain, Mark E. F. Kerr, M. V. O.</item>
                        <item>Flag lieutenant, Gerald Sowerby.</item>
                        <item>Secretary, Edward H. Shearme.</item>
                        <item>Engineer commander, William F. Pamphlett.</item>
                    </list>
                    <pb facs="0598" n="478" xml:id="pg_478"/>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="italic">Captains of ships of second cruiser squadron.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <list>
                        <item>Charles H. Robertson, C. M. G., M. V. O., H. M. S. <hi rend="italic"
                                >Cornwall</hi>.</item>
                        <item>Richard B. Farquhar, H. M. S. <hi rend="italic">Essex</hi>.</item>
                        <item>Richard H. Peirse, M. V. O., H. M. S. <hi rend="italic"
                            >Bedford</hi>.</item>
                        <item>Charles H. Dare, M. V. O., H. M. S. <hi rend="italic"
                            >Berwick</hi>.</item>
                        <item>Herbert G. King Hall, D. S. O., H. M. S. <hi rend="italic"
                                >Cumberland.</hi>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
